    "narrative": "The Austin Waves head into today\u2019s slate with **Kyle Tucker** and **Jackson Merrill** serving as the core offensive anchors. **Kyle Tucker** is our highest-rated start at 76.67, benefiting significantly from a favorable matchup against Colin Rea and wind conditions that offer a +5% boost to his already elite base projection. Similarly, **Jackson Merrill** earns a robust 70.91 rating; while we are monitoring a 36% rain risk, his favorable platoon split and prime #3 spot in the order make him an essential start against Zac Gallen. **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** also provides top-tier production (67.40) today, as his power profile aligns perfectly with favorable park factors and a productive spot in the lineup against Joey Cantillo.\n\nEfficiency remains the priority as we balance game caps, leading to a difficult bench decision regarding **Marcell Ozuna**. With a score of 47.28, **Marcell Ozuna** was the strongest candidate to crack the starting nine but fell just short due to the Optimizer prioritizing the positional utility of **Andy Pages** and **Dominic Smith** in specific platoon matchups. **Andy Pages** (59.97) earns his spot through a high-upside matchup against Colin Rea, and while we acknowledge the threat of an elite arm like Zack Wheeler, we are trusting **Dominic Smith** (41.31) to leverage his BvP history and platoon edge to provide marginal value. Elsewhere, **Gunnar Henderson** faces a stiff test against Crochet; his 53.08 score is buoyed by park factors, but we are tempering expectations given the elite SP skill of his opponent. All managers should keep a close eye on the final lineups, as the projected statuses for **Drake Baldwin**, **Miguel Vargas**, **Nasim Nunez**, **Jacob Wilson**, and **Josh Jung** remain fluid.",
